<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NETNEWS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INTERNETTERS REACT TO WORLD CUP 
</HEADLINE>
   (Charles Stough is an editor at the Dayton (Ohio) Daily News)  
 By CHARLES STOUGH   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Something like 1.5 billion people around the world watched the
final World Cup soccer game Sunday (France over Brazil, 3-0).
</P>
<P>
   Minutes after the final whistle, the Monday-morning
quarterbacking began on the Internet. (Monday-morning
quarterbacking? That's an American football term. It means
second-guessing the game, a sport favored by couch potatoes who
never get close to the field.)
</P>
<P>
   The early opinions were posted in the Usenet newsgroup
alt.sports.soccer.worldcup98, where the argument certainly will
rage for days. Samples:
</P>
<P>
   _``Why didn't Brazil play football tonight? It was too easy for
France! A boring final!''
</P>
<P>
   _``It is exactly how (the Brazilians) have been playing for the
last couple of years, and they never deserved to get to the final
game. There are so many better teams than Brazil.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Have you seen the last few World Cup finals? This one was a
miracle compared to those. France actually played some flowing
football in the first half.''
</P>
<P>
   _``How much would England have won that final?''
</P>
<P>
   _``Oh here we go _English sportsmanship at its best. Someone
better tell him England can't get to the final without winning.''
</P>
<P>
   _``The French should be congratulated. They staged a well
organized tournament and an excellent final. They deserve it and
I'm glad for them.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Again the `what if' questions. England had a decent squad but
certainly not a magical one. People seem to forget that before the
penalty loss to Argentina, England were well beaten by Romania.
Does this make Romania more worthy a World Cup winner than
England?''
</P>
<P>
   _``If England (had won) the World Cup they would have rioted and
tipped over the Eiffel Tower.''
</P>
<P>
   _``I must say after watching all the games and hearing most of
the comentary on this world cup, Brazil were made out to be virtual
supermen but, alas, they were exposed. Well, if you beat weak teams
you would obviously look good .... France on the other hand
stumbled along slowly, playing well, averagely and also scraping
out a victory against Italy, but unlike Brazil their defence is
tops and deserved to be called world class.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Well said. France put on an excellent display _especially in
the first half .... The French were not at all intimidated by the
Brazilians and ran at them from the beginning _consequently
exposing Brazil's lack of cohesion (which some of the fawning
press, in unconditional worship of Brazil, failed to remark on).
</P>
<P>
   ``The hosts have won, setting France alight and adding a new
name to the short list of World Cup victors. Felicitations les
blues!''
</P>
<P>
   Charles Stough is an editor for the Dayton (Ohio) Daily News.
</P>
<P>
   His electronic address is copyboy(at)dma.org.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
