<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Top Road Destinations
 &HT;    Sidebar to ROAD-LEAD
 &HT;    By Palm Beach Post Staffwriters
 &HT;    c. 1998 Palm Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Wondering where your neighbors are driving to this year?
</P>
<P>
   A good bet is Disney World. It's the No. 1 travel destination in
the world. Moms and dads on other parts of the globe are making a
beeline there, too.
</P>
<P>
   The top five destinations (in descending order) by car,
according to the AAA Auto Club South, are:
</P>
<P>
   _ Orlando
</P>
<P>
   _ Los Angeles/Anaheim
</P>
<P>
   _ Las Vegas
</P>
<P>
   _ Myrtle Beach, S.C.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Great Smoky Mountains
</P>
<P>
   The top domestic air travel destinations are similar: Orlando,
Las Vegas, Los Angeles, Hawaii and California. For international
travel, London is in the No. 1 spot, followed by Cancun, Mexico;
Vancouver, British Columbia; Paris; and Rome.
</P>
