How many true millionaires do we have in the Miami Valley and how
are they spending their money? Are we reliving the 50s or have we
surpassed it? (Gulliver, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   FIRE-SURVEY _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ In 1989, state foresters
visited the woody lots of Palm Coast and asked its residents:
exactly how afraid of wildfire are you? Going door to door, they
handed out 200 surveys to homes most likely to burn if a blaze
broke out. Only 94 bothered to answer. Those who did conceded fire
was their biggest natural enemy. But the chance of a fire actually
occurring over the next 10 years, they wagered, was less than
fifty-fifty. (Staletovich, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
