<P>
   BRODY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Just when dermatologists and cancer
specialists had Americans convinced that sunscreens could protect
them from skin cancer and wrinkles, a scientist at Memorial
Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center in New York concluded after a review
of available research that sunscreens might not prevent melanoma,
the deadliest form of skin cancer, at least not the way products
were formulated and used in the 1980s. (1250 words) By Jane E.
Brody. (``l'' code)
