today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
KIDS-BUSINESS (Los Angeles) _ From an Internet-based virtual stock
market simulation game for teen-agers to business summer camps that
teach kids the finer points of no-load mutual funds, there's an
unparalleled supply of entrepreneurial resources for teen-agers and
young adults 21 and younger. By Heesun Wee. 
. 
KIDBIZ-SIDEBAR (Los Angeles) No matter what the age of the
entrepreneur, common factors play a role in tipping a new venture
toward success. Jennifer Kushell, founder and president of the
Boston-based Young Entrepreneurs Network, cautioned beginners from
jumping into already saturated markets. By Heesun Wee. 

