<HEADLINE>
HATS ON!  
 (HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A swimsuit and sun block are essential on the beach,
and so is a hat with a protective brim.
</P>
<P>
   Wide-brimmed straws by Burke-Leggi include two trimmed with
striped ribbon ($190 each), one with a big bow ($200) and one with
a fabric peony ($195). All at the Hat Shop, 120 Thompson Street
(Spring Street).
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has natural-color straws with leather bands by
Henry Beguelin ($150) and with black- or white-cord trimming by
Annabell Ingall ($135), and white hats with silk-screened flowers
by Miss Jones ($250).
</P>
<P>
   Princess Foufou's striped cotton fisherman's hat ($60) and pale
lavender cotton hat with a self bow ($75) are at Saks Fifth Avenue,
which also has a black-and-natural-striped straw hat by Kokin
($120), a lime green straw with appliqued daisies by Andrea Stuart
($75), and a leopard print ($275) and a packable hat in cafe au
lait with a self bow ($225), both by Eric Javits.
