<SLUG> BC-KIDBIZ-SIDEBAR-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GETTING OF THE GROUND
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HEESUN WEE 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; No matter what the age of the entrepreneur,
common factors play a role in tipping a new venture toward success.
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer Kushell, founder and president of the Boston-based
Young Entrepreneurs Network, cautioned beginners from jumping into
already saturated markets. In the technology industry, for example,
it's common to stumble across several Web site development
companies in the same neighborhood. And too many vendors offering
the same services can mean a tougher, more competitive battle for
profits and overall success.
</P>
<P>
   Jessica Ferretti, 17, of Glendale offered this bit of advice:
Don't underestimate the importance of a clear business plan.
</P>
<P>
   Ferretti knows first-hand what needs to happen after that
brilliant idea hits _ a big investment of time and work. Her
efforts this year toward a business plan for a child-care referral
service paid off when she won a national business plan competition
sponsored by An Income of Her Own, a national, nonprofit
organization based in Burbank that's devoted to teaching
entrepreneurial skills to teen-age girls and young women.
</P>
<P>
   ``The disadvantage is it may take time away from school or other
extracurricular interests. The advantage is helping people out and
making money, and learning to work with people and children,'' said
Ferretti, who is hoping to get the business off the ground in about
a year.
</P>
<P>
   Young entrepreneurs have lots of resources to lend them a hand:
</P>
<P>
   The Young Entrepreneurs Network can be reached at (617)
867-4690. Their Web site at www.yenetwork.com.
</P>
<P>
   _An Income of Her Own in Burbank offers entrepreneurial
resources for teen-age girls and young women ages 14 to 19. Call
them at (818) 842-3040, or visit their Web site at
www.incomeofherown.com.
</P>
<P>
   _Visit the U.S. Small Business Administration or SBA Web site at
www.sbaonline.sba.gov.
</P>
<P>
   And lots of teens and young adults have heeded the call to run
their own businesses. Here are a few young entrepreneurs with
products to try:
</P>
<P>
   _Dramatic Designs in Calabasas can be reached at (818) 591-1967,
or e-mail them at DDesignsCAaol.com.
</P>
<P>
   _Cinnamon Cat's Baked Goods in Chatsworth can be reached at
(818) 993-4460 for orders.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
