BIKING (Langton) w/art _ An off-road profile on the Red Rock to
Calabasas Peak ride, known for some stunning rock outcroppings and
panoramic views of Topanga Canyon and Stunt Road. It's not that
technical, but there are a couple of really steep sections, as well
as some pavement riding on Old Topanga. The view alone is worth the
ride, but it's also a test of hillclimbing power and fitness. It
was also the location of the Santa Monica Mountains Conservancy
meeting that forced the creation of CORBA; this would provide a
nice little aside.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
FANTAIL (Matthews) w/art, map _ From the time the first snowplow
clears the road over Tioga Pass into Yosemite National Park each
summer, straight through to Oct. 31 close of trout season, crowds
of anglers hammer Saddlebag, Tioga and Ellery lakes and Lee Vining
Creek on a daily basis. And for good reason. Each of the waters
have strong populations of wild brown, rainbow and brook trout, and
bi-weekly plants of catchable trout are made by the Department of
Fish and Game to ensure the fishery remains healthy. However, if
you come to the Eastern Sierra for solace and a pristine mountain
experience, that isn't what you'll likely find at these instensely
popular roadside jumping-off spots. The good news is that solitude
is just a short walk away, at Fantail Lake.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
BACKPAK (Pauly) _ The difficulties finding an early-season
backpacking desitination that isn't accessible due to snow, roaring
river crossing and damaged or missing bridges. Call Dave Provins,
Boy Scout Tropp 211 leader, who has had a heck of a time finding an
adequate four-day trip in the Sierra, (818) 882-8066.
</P>
