</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following financial
news stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Tuesday, July 14, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Tom Hicks at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   LA-AREA-HOMES (Los Angeles) _ In the first sign of a broad-based
recovery for the housing market, sales of single-family homes in
the San Fernando and Santa Clarita valleys soared in June. By
Deborah Adamson.
</P>
<P>
   WHITTAKER-SHARES (Los Angeles) _ In a sign that Whittaker
Corp.'s future has brightened, Tannenbaum &AMP; Co. LLD bumped up its
stake in the Simi Valley, Calif.-based developer of fluid control
and fire-safety systems. By Enrique Rivero.
</P>
<P>
   MENACE-VIDEO (Los Angeles) _ Warner Bros. releases ``Dennis the
Menace Strikes Again'' starring Don Rickles and Betty White, among
others, as a direct-to-video release, underscoring the growing
popularity of bypassing movie theaters with easy-to-recognize
properties. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Ken LLoyd, Ph.D., a specialist in
organizational behavior, answers questions on getting ahead and
getting along in today's business world.
</P>
</TEXT>
