<HEADER>
A3033 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     07-13 0739
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROMANTIC AND INTELLECTUAL PURSUITS
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   J &UR; osh Brolin &LR; , 30-year-old actor and son of  &UR; James Brolin &LR; , is
dating  &UR; Pamela Anderson &LR; , reports New Weekly magazine _ and why
shouldn't an Australian magazine be an authority on this subject? _
which raises the prospect of  &UR; Barbra Streisand &LR;  becoming Anderson's
mother-in-law.
</P>
<P>
   _ At last, the periodical you've been waiting for: Macauley's
Historical Essays. This volume, published in 1890, was checked out
of the North Beach Branch of the San Francisco library several days
before the great quake of April 18, 1906, kept out all these
years, &LR;  and returned, along with two others, during a recent
library-fine amnesty.
</P>
<P>
   The returnees _ which, &LR;  without amnesty would have fetched
something like $11,000 in fines for the library _ will be displayed
at the History Center of the Main Library.
</P>
<P>
   _ Among the Personals ads in the latest issue of the New York
Review of Books (and good luck to one and all): ``All fetishes,
domination/submission fantasies explored by Ivy League educated
Goddess''; ``organizer of world revolutions, at age 80 ... (seeks)
warm companion for next 30 or more years activity'';
``enchantress'' from New Mexico ``temporarily relocating to
Pittsburgh.''
</P>
<P>
   _ In what planners believe will be the first karaoke wedding
ever,  &UR; John Stadlberger  &LR; and  &UR; Martha Rodriguez &LR;  are getting hitched
later this month at Yet Wah restaurant in Diamond Heights. The
ceremony will be presided over by  &UR; Ben Fong-Torres &LR; , a mail-order
minister as well as regular karaoke emcee on Tuesday nights at Yet
Wah.
</P>
<P>
   After vows are exchanged, the bride will sing ``(I Love You) for
Sentimental Reasons,'' and the groom will sing back ``Baby, I Love
Your Way.'' The couple met at the restaurant in 1992.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Nervous habits of celebrities is the focus of a hard-hitting
investigative report in the latest issue of Good Housekeeping,
which reveals that  &UR; Kathie Lee Gifford &LR;  ``is a habitual tooth
licker.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Gordon Bergman &LR;  noticed that the doctors' newspaper ad for
Viagra, which featured the grinning face of  &UR; Dwight Eisenhower &LR; ,
has a new icon:  &UR; Winston Churchill &LR;  giving the V sign and the logo
``Victory at Last.''
</P>
<P>
   _ The Earth Island Journal, which is always fretting about
something, warns that when high-definition TV _ to be broadcast
across the country beginning in November _ was tested in Texas,
radiation knocked out 60 wireless heart monitors at the Baylor
University Medical Center in Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spy food and Web site cases not quite closed:  &UR; Nick Chase &LR; 
offers the irresistible Dr. No Anchovies; and  &UR; Strange de Jim &LR; 
notes that while whitehouse.gov gets you  &UR; Bill Clinton &LR;  &AMP; Co.,
replacing the `gov' with a `com' gets you something very much else.
</P>
<P>
   _ Responding to the trendy renaissance of cigar smoking among
young people, the American Cancer Society has begun an anti-cigar
ad campaign, &LR;  using a series of ``Generation Gullible'' images,
each incorporating the tag line, ``Is This Fad Worth Dying For?''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OUT AND ABOUT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Sparky &LR; 's wondering about the name of Gandhi Restaurant in San
Mateo: ``Why would one name an eatin' place after a man who's
famous for not choosing to? Gives `fast' food a whole new
meaning.'' And  &UR; Steve Waye &LR;  overheard a young food critic
expressing himself on 24th Street: ``But Mama, I don't like
focaccia!''
</P>
<P>
   In Walnut Creek,  &UR; Y. Lowe &LR;  saw a bumper sticker that read
``Visualize No Liberals.'' Furthermore,  &UR; Chris Morano &LR;  and  &UR; Jimmy &LR; 
 &UR; Jarrett &LR; , sticklers for accuracy, point out that the new Mel's
Drive-In (on Van Ness in San Francisco) isn't, ``unless one intends
to park in the lobby'' of the hotel next door.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile,  &UR; Matt Buka  &LR; proclaims himself a charter member of
Wait Watchers, a support group for Muni passengers. Finally,
 &UR; Randy Alfred &LR;  is awestruck by the multicultural marquee of the
Castro Theatre, which now proclaims: ``18th SF Jewish Film Festival
July 16-24'' and ``Beach Party w/ &UR; Troy Donahue &LR;  &AMP;  &UR; Sandra &LR; 
 &UR; Dee &LR;  July 17.'' The explanation for how this particular sandwich
got made _ seeded rye on top and bottom and American cheese in the
middle _ is that serious Jews don't do movies on Friday nights.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Q: What is your motto? A: `What' is my motto.''
</P>
<P>
   _ David Bowie in Vanity Fair.
</P>
