<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, JULY 14
</HEADLINE>
  Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CHINA-SUMMIT-NYT (moved on Monday, June 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 29,
about President Clinton's arrival in Shanghai referred incorrectly
to the new Shanghai Children's Medical Center, which was on Hillary
Rodham Clinton's itinerary. It is not the first hospital in China
devoted to treating children.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MANZANAR-NATIONAL-SITE-NYT (moved on Friday, June 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, June 19,
about the development of the Manzanar internment camp in California
as a national historic site defined the term ``nisei'' incorrectly.
It denotes the children of Japanese immigrants, not all
Japanese-Americans.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-EASTER-ISLAND-NYT (moved on Monday, June 6)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 6,
about mysterious statues on Easter Island, Chile, referred
incorrectly to Kon-Tiki, the raft used by an explorer to show that
Indians from South America could have reached the island. It was
made primarily of balsa logs, not reeds.
</P>
<P>
   BC-EIFFEL-TOWER-SALE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, July 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, July 7,
about an American group's proposed acquisition of a stake in Credit
Foncier de France, which has an interest in the company that
operates the Eiffel Tower, misidentified an American investor. It
is the Bass Group, an investment group led by Robert M. Bass _ not
the Bass brothers _ that is joining the GMAC Commercial Mortgage
Corporation in buying the stake.
</P>
</TEXT>
