</P>
<P>
   REMANUFACTURE (Undated) _ Once the purview of myriad small
companies that eked out a living refurbishing carburetors, printer
cartridges and other used parts, re-manufacturing _ a method of
re-using old parts in new machines _ has hit corporate America in a
big way. By Claudia H. Deutsch.
